          h4.mb64.uppercase Importance of Budgeting
        p.lead.m32.pb32 Budgeting provides an estimation of your business’s cash flow, of both revenues reaped and expenses paid. Budgeting uses estimation to quantify the expectation of revenues a business wants to achieve for a future period, usually over a fiscal year. It represents a business’s financial position and it helps provide a direction where the business wants to go. To be a successful player in today's environment, one has to have a robust budgeting & forecasting system. Businesses would need to:
      
        ul.lead data-bullet="ti-check-box"
          li Know your cashflow and other resources requirement
          li Plan and prepare for any contingencies
          li Set goals and targets for key management personnel
          li Drawing up growth strategy and identifying milestones

